channel.title: Strange silab V4 error
channel.description:
Okay, well I cleared my .mpr_file_store_32 file, and then i loaded up silabs V4 client, since the items are still working on it, and after it downloads the cache, it closes and the client cmd has this error and if i close that and start nit up again it just says "some strange error has occured, please tell silabsoft" can anyone help, or recoginize the error and know what to do, if so, thanks alot
[code]C:\Documents and Settings\Robert.ORION\Desktop>java -Xmx500m -jar client.jar 0 0 highmem members 0 RS2 user client - release #317 silabsoft.org java.io.FileNotFoundException: c:\windows\.mpr_file_store_32\vanhat (Access is d enied) at java.io.FileOutputStream.open(Native Method) at java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(Unknown Source) at java.io.FileOutputStream.<init>(Unknown Source) at sc.a(sc.java) at sc.a(sc.java) at sc.<init>(sc.java) at client.a(client.java) at client.b(client.java) at a.run(a.java) at client.run(client.java) at java.lang.Thread.run(Unknown Source) Some strange error occured, please tell silabsoft about it.
C:\Documents and Settings\Robert.ORION\Desktop>pause Press any key to continue . . . [/code]
